        oneLinerFr: "Le pipeline complet qui fait répondre l'IA à partir de vos documents plutôt que de son imagination — la technique que vous avez construite aujourd'hui.",
        explanation: "RAG is the entire 5-stage pipeline you watched run in the Pipeline Visualiser: Query → Embed → Search → Rerank → Generate. Instead of asking GPT-4o 'What is Air Canada's bereavement policy?' and hoping it remembers correctly from its training data (which is how the original chatbot worked — and failed), you first search your own documents for relevant chunks, then give those chunks to GPT-4o along with the question. The model can only answer from what you give it.\n\nThis is the fundamental shift from 'AI that knows things' to 'AI that reads things.' The Air Canada chatbot that Jake Moffatt encountered had no RAG pipeline. It generated from training patterns — patterns that included bereavement policies from other airlines — and fabricated a policy that didn't exist. A RAG-enabled version of that same chatbot would have: (1) received Jake's question, (2) searched Air Canada's actual policy documents, (3) found the chunk saying 'bereavement fares must be requested AT THE TIME OF BOOKING,' and (4) generated a response citing that specific document.\n\nYou built exactly this system today. When you uploaded the four Air Canada documents (bereavement policy, chatbot transcript, tribunal ruling, refund FAQ), embedded them into vector space, and ran a query through the Pipeline Visualiser, you were running a RAG pipeline. The system retrieved the relevant chunks, passed them to GPT-4o, and generated a grounded response with citations [1], [2], [3].\n\nRAG is not a product or a tool — it's a pattern. Any time you put documents between the user's question and the model's response, you're doing RAG. The quality depends on how well you execute each stage: how you chunk, how you embed, how many chunks you retrieve, whether you rerank, and what system prompt you give the generation model. These are the 12 levers you configured in the Configure tab.",
